8.Write a query to display all orders and their corresponding customer details, 
  if available. Include orders even if there is no matching customer in the customer table.

ANS:
SQL> SELECT*FROM CUSTOMERS C1 RIGHT OUTER JOIN ORDERS O1 ON  O1.ORDERID=C1.CUSTOMERID;

CUSTOMERID CUSTOMRNAM    ORDERID CUSTOMERID ORDERDATE  TOTAMOUNT
---------- ---------- ---------- ---------- --------- ----------
                             105            27-APR-24        300
                             104          1 08-MAR-24        600
                             101          1 12-JAN-24        850
                             103          4 22-DEC-24        700
                             102          2 18-MAR-24        900
                             106          2 16-APR-24       1000

6 rows selected.

9.Write a query to display all the customers and all orders, including customers
  without orders and orders without customers ?

ANS:
SQL> SELECT O.ORDERID, O.ORDERDATE, O.CUSTOMERID FROM ORDERS O LEFT JOIN CUSTOMERS C ON O.CUSTOMERID=C.CUSTOMERID WHERE C.CUSTOMERID IS NULL;

   ORDERID ORDERDATE CUSTOMERID
---------- --------- ----------
       105 27-APR-24


